Charles P. Verdon of California has been nominated to be Deputy Administrator for Defense Programs at the National Nuclear Security Administration, Department of Energy. He currently holds the position of Principal Associate Director at the Weapons and Complex Integration Directorate at Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory. Dr. Verdon has a background in nuclear engineering and has received recognition from the American Physical Society for his work in plasma physics research. President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to designate an individual as Chairperson of the United States Semiquincentennial Commission, but the specific person has not been mentioned in the article.